    Serialized Form

    • Package view.gamePanelViews

      • Class view.gamePanelViews.GameView

        class GameView extends JPanel implements Serializable

        • Serialized Fields

          • enemyView
            EnemyView enemyView
            reference to the EnemyView, used to render all the enemies in the current room
          • fps
            double fps
            the total frames / second text. it is used the GameView.paintComponent(Graphics) method to track the fps on the top left corner
          • fpsFont
            Font fpsFont
            font used to display the fps on the top left corner
          • frameCount
            int frameCount
            numbers of frames that have passed.
          • gameFont
            Font gameFont
            font used to display the game text, such as the top right's world info and the interaction prompt of the player.
          • interactableObjectsView
            InteractableObjectsView interactableObjectsView
            reference to the InteractableObjectsView, use to render all the interactable objects in the room
          • inventoryView
            InventoryView inventoryView
            reference to the InventoryView, used to render the player's inventory
          • lastFpsTime
            long lastFpsTime
            used to track the fps.
          • levelManager
            LevelManager levelManager
            reference to the LevelManager model, used to get the data of the current depth, level, and room type.
          • levelView
            LevelView levelView
            reference to the LevelView, used to render the tiles in the game.
          • player
            Player player
            reference to the Player model, used to get the player's extraction status so that the ResultScreenView can appear accordingly and the interaction prompt to appear when the player is near an interactable object.
          • playerView
            PlayerView playerView
            reference to the PlayerView, used to render the player
          • resultScreenView
            ResultScreenView resultScreenView
            reference to the ResultScreenView, used to render the result screen when the player extracts.
          • window
            JFrame window
            reference to the JFrame window created in Main

      • Class view.gamePanelViews.LeaderboardView

        class LeaderboardView extends JPanel implements Serializable

        • Serialized Fields

          • exitFont
            Font exitFont
            font used to the display the exit prompt on the bottom right of the leaderboard screen.
          • fontPath
            String fontPath
            path of the font used, in the res folder
          • leaderboard
            Leaderboard leaderboard
            reference to the Leaderboard model, used to get the data of the leaderboard to render.
          • leaderboardFont
            Font leaderboardFont
            font used to display the leaderboard contents, such as placing, name and points.
          • leaderboardTitleFont
            Font leaderboardTitleFont
            font used to display the leaderboard title on the top.
          • padding
            int padding
            visual padding integer that helps with the spacing consistency of the leaderboard screen.

      • Class view.gamePanelViews.PauseMenuView

        class PauseMenuView extends JPanel implements Serializable

        • Serialized Fields

          • options
            String[] options
            the available options in the pause menu. there a 2 currently available: 'resume' and 'to the main menu'
          • pauseMenuFont
            Font pauseMenuFont
            font used for the options in the pause menu
          • pauseMenuTitleFont
            Font pauseMenuTitleFont
            font used in the title of the pause menu, the 'game paused' section.
          • selectedOption
            int selectedOption
            the currently selected option in the pause menu. it is updated via PauseMenuView.selectNextOption() and PauseMenuView.selectPreviousOption()

      • Class view.gamePanelViews.ResultScreenView

        class ResultScreenView extends JPanel implements Serializable

        • Serialized Fields

          • grandTotalFont
            Font grandTotalFont
            font that is used to display the 'grand total points' at the end.
          • multiplierFont
            Font multiplierFont
            font that is used to display the 'multipliers' title before the multipliers.
          • padding
            int padding
            visual padding integer that helps with the spacing consistency of the result screen.
          • player
            Player player
            reference to the Player model. to get the that player's instance's ScoreTracker model.
          • resultFont
            Font resultFont
            default font used to display the results of the player. the font is used to display the total interactable objects opened, card points, the total points got from the interactable objects + card points and the multipliers.
          • scoreTracker
            ScoreTracker scoreTracker
            reference to the ScoreTracker model. this is where all the score info is taken from to display the result screen.
          • titleFont
            Font titleFont
            font used to display the 'extraction completed' title on top of the screen.

      • Class view.gamePanelViews.TitleScreenView

        class TitleScreenView extends JPanel implements Serializable

        • Serialized Fields

          • menuFont
            Font menuFont
            the menu font, of the TitleScreenView.options
          • options
            String[] options
            contains the menu option that are displayed in the title screen
          • selectedFont
            Font selectedFont
            the font of the currently selected font. note that is slightly bigger than the TitleScreenView.menuFont, so that the used has an even better clarity of the current selected option.
          • selectedOption
            int selectedOption
            the currently selected option, it can be incremented or decremented via TitleScreenView.selectNextOption() and TitleScreenView.selectPreviousOption().

      • Class view.gamePanelViews.WhatsYourNameView

        class WhatsYourNameView extends JPanel implements Serializable

        • Serialized Fields

          • displayedName
            String displayedName
            represents the currently displayed name.
          • fontPath
            String fontPath
            the path of the .ttf file in res folder
          • nameTypedInFont
            Font nameTypedInFont
            font used to display the currently typed in name. the font is loaded via WhatsYourNameView.loadFont(String, float) method.
          • padding
            int padding
            a fixed integer, that is the 'padding' to allow a consistent alignment of the text
          • whatsYourNameFont
            Font whatsYourNameFont
            font used to display the title that says 'what's your name?'. the font is loaded via WhatsYourNameView.loadFont(String, float) method.
